Transcription.Text: The directional angle of the scanner could be adjusted to cover any particular area within its range. Geoffrey turned the scale slowly to cover the ground immediately ahead. He was able to pick out towns, unrecognisable to the naked eye, obscured by the ground haze which even on the clearest night limited angular vision.
